Kunle Adeyanju, the brave Nigerian traveling from London to Lagos State, Nigeria, has made remarkable progress on his journey as he approaches the shores of Africa. The news came as a surprise to all doubters who thought the journey was impossible.
The journey, which he started last Tuesday, is expected to last for 25 days. Within the first six days, he has been able to make it to the shores of Africa. He said the reason he embarked on the charity journey was to generate some funds so he could use them to create a good source of water and other welfare packages for the people of Africa.
ALSO READ:Â Netizens react as Nigerian man sets out from London on bike, plans to reach Lagos in 25 days
According to the information available at the moment, Mr. Kunle Adeyanju has entered the shores of Africa and is currently close to Casablanca, a city in Morocco. He made this announcement earlier today, April 25, 2022, on his Twitter handle.


